{"name":"Pile of Bones and Corpses","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/commodities/bones/bones-skull-white.webp","system":{"description":"<p>A large cave in the wolves' lair filled with bones and human corpses - the grim remains of the pack's victims. The sight is disturbing and serves as evidence of the wolves' brutality and the danger they pose to Durfort's inhabitants.</p>","notes":"","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"","source":"Red Hood Iskra","category":"scenario","scenario":"Red Hood Iskra","requirement":"","scenarioSlug":"red-hood-iskra"},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"source":"Red Hood Iskra","category":"scenario","scenario":"Red Hood Iskra","scenarioSlug":"red-hood-iskra","sourceDirectory":"red-hood-iskra","legacyId":"BonesPile","legacyType":"descriptor","folderName":"Red Hood Iskra"}},"_id":"X4HMNGa7RFZ8gEUP"}
{"name":"Secret Passageway Map","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/sundries/documents/blueprint-axe.webp","system":{"description":"<p>Knowledge of a secret passageway that connects the large dining room to the inner courtyard of the Dubois Palace. This hidden route was used by Iskra and the wolf pack to launch their surprise attack on the mansion. The passageway may also connect to the underground tunnel leading from the wolves' den to the old well in Durfort's main square.</p>","notes":"","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"","source":"Red Hood Iskra","category":"scenario","scenario":"Red Hood Iskra","requirement":"","scenarioSlug":"red-hood-iskra"},"flags":{"broken-tales":{"source":"Red Hood Iskra","category":"scenario","scenario":"Red Hood Iskra","scenarioSlug":"red-hood-iskra","sourceDirectory":"red-hood-iskra","legacyId":"SecretPassageway","legacyType":"descriptor","folderName":"Red Hood Iskra"}},"_id":"jOMeQ0fMOa8IjG28"}
